  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "5rHCUJkv4MV+3A1RcwRBftQagm4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Claim\nOffline-edit durability is provided by PGlite + the outbox cursor: the local reactor keeps working, and on reconnect the cursor replays accumulated ops to Swarm.\n\n## Flow\n1. User edits documents while Bee node is unreachable.\n2. Operations accumulate in PGlite (local reactor works fine).\n3. SwarmChannel connection state transitions to `error` \u2192 push is blocked.\n4. User reconnects Bee node \u2192 state becomes `connected`.\n5. Outbox cursor catches up: all accumulated ops are pushed to Swarm.\n6. No data loss \u2014 cursors in PGlite track exactly what was synced.\n\n## Why this is safe\n- The cursor is only advanced after a successful feed write, so a crash mid-push is idempotent.\n- The local reactor is the source of truth; Swarm is purely a mirror.\n- User never loses work due to Bee downtime.\n\n## Source\nSwarm Channel Architecture, \"Flow 4: Offline Edits \u2192 Reconnect\".",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:38.000Z"
    }
  },
